A)	Write a MongoDB query to create and drop database. 

> show databases  // checks currents databases. 
> use mks   // Using database mks 
> db.createCollection("user")   //Creating Empty Collection 
> show databases     //Database is Created 
> db.dropDatabase()     //Drop Database 



B)	Write a MongoDB query to create, display and drop a collection 

> use sy 
> db.user.insertOne({ "name": "ABC", "rollno": 10 }) 
> show collections 
> db.user.find() 
> db.user.drop() 
> show collections 



C)	Write a MongoDB query to insert, query, update and delete a document 


i.	Insert  Document  
> use mks 
>  db.products.insert( { item: "card", qty: 15 } ) 
> db.products.find()


ii.	Insert Multiple Documents 
>  db.products.insert([ 
   { _id: 11, item: "pencil", qty: 50, type: "no.2" }, 
   { item: "pen", qty: 20 }, 
   { item: "eraser", qty: 25 } 
   ]) 
> db.col.insertOne({ "name": "John", "age": 25 })


•	Updating Document Queries : 
iv.	Updating Document using $set 
Fetching Record with _id:10 and Updating status from “A” to “Pending” 
> db.inventory.find({ "_id": 10 })
> db.inventory.update(
  { _id: 10 },
  { $set: { status: "Pending" } }
  )
> db.inventory.find({ "_id": 10 })


. Updating Document with overwriting. 
> db.product.find()
> db.product.updateOne(
  { "item": "pen" },           // filter
  { $set: { "qty": 400, "COD": "Yes" } }  // only update these fields
  )
> db.product.find()


•	Deleting Document 
•	Removing Document By Key: Value Pair Reference 
> db.products.find()
> db.products.deleteOne({ "item": "pen" })
> db.products.find()
> db.products.remove({ qty: { $gt: 2 } })
> db.products.find()












